Is there any role more difficult for an actor to play convincingly than the role of a bad actor, especially if you want to play the role in a way that is entertaining?   This is one of Vincent Price's finest moments, and an elegant, literate, and fun horror movie.

Unfortunately, no one is seeding this right now.  I'm going to keep the torrent open, in case it ever comes back.
